		<title>Republicans win Obamacare legal challenge, add to insurer concerns</title>

		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Three competing plans for battling a potential Zika virus outbreak in the United States were presented on the floor of the U.S. Senate on Thursday, as lawmakers tried to break an impasse pitting President Barack Obama against congressional Republicans.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>New Alabama law could shutter two abortion clinics near schools</title>

		<title>Car door windows don't stop UV rays</title>

		<title>WHO recommends new test, treatment plan for superbug strains of TB</title>


		<description>The World Health Organization on Thursday recommended a speedier, cheaper treatment plan for patients with superbug forms of tuberculosis (TB) - a change that should help cure thousands of the killer disease.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>How much palliative care breast cancer patients get may depend on race</title>


		<description>(Reuters Health) - When women have advanced breast cancer, the amount of comfort-oriented care they receive at the end of life may depend on the color of their skin, a small U.S. study suggests.<div class="feedflare">

		<title>Patient awareness of antibiotic resistance and its prevention is low</title>
